qas.question: What was different between the polish nobility and others?

answers.text: European countries the nobility lost power as the ruler strove for absolute monarchy

qas.question: What happened to nobility at expense of the king?
What did the political system eventually evolve into?
What did the ruler strive for?

context: The Polish nobility differed in many respects from the nobility of other countries. The most important difference was that, while in most <a0_0>European countries the nobility lost power as the ruler strove for <a3_0>absolute monarchy<a3_0/><a0_0/>, in Poland the reverse process occurred: the nobility <a1_0>actually gained power<a1_0/> at the expense of the king, and the political system evolved into an <a2_0>oligarchy<a2_0/>.
